---
/**
 * Terms of Service Page
 *
 * Stand for Hemp - Terms of service for the advocacy platform
 */

import LandingLayout from '../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
---

<LandingLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Stand for Hemp"
  description="Terms of service for Stand for Hemp advocacy platform"
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-reading">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8" style="color: var(--color-soil-dark);">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-8">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 2025
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-soil-dark);">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Acceptance of Terms
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            By accessing and using Stand for Hemp ("the Platform"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
            If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Purpose of the Platform
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            Stand for Hemp is a grassroots advocacy platform designed to help Americans contact their elected
            representatives about hemp-related legislation. We provide tools to facilitate civic engagement and
            democratic participation.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            User Conduct
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            When using the Platform, you agree to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Provide accurate information when contacting representatives</li>
            <li>Use the Platform for lawful advocacy purposes only</li>
            <li>Not abuse, harass, threaten, or intimidate others</li>
            <li>Not send spam or automated messages through our tools</li>
            <li>Not attempt to interfere with the Platform's operation or security</li>
            <li>Respect the rights of others and act in good faith</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Advocacy Messages
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            When you send messages to representatives through the Platform:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>You are responsible for the content of your messages</li>
            <li>We provide suggested language, but you can customize messages as you see fit</li>
            <li>Your messages will be sent to the representatives you select</li>
            <li>We do not guarantee that representatives will read or respond to your messages</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            No Warranties
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            The Platform is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Uninterrupted or error-free operation</li>
            <li>That messages will reach their intended recipients</li>
            <li>Any specific outcomes from using the Platform</li>
            <li>The accuracy or completeness of representative contact information</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Limitation of Liability
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, Stand for Hemp and its operators shall not be liable for:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages</li>
            <li>Loss of profits, data, or use of the Platform</li>
            <li>Damages resulting from your use or inability to use the Platform</li>
            <li>Actions taken by representatives or third parties</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Intellectual Property
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            The Platform's content, design, logos, and materials are protected by intellectual property laws.
            You may not copy, modify, or distribute our content without permission. However, we encourage you
            to share links to the Platform to spread awareness.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Third-Party Services
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            The Platform may use third-party services (such as representative lookup APIs). We are not responsible
            for the availability, accuracy, or policies of these third-party services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Termination
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to the Platform for any user who violates these
            terms or engages in abusive behavior.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Changes to Terms
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We may modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the Platform after changes constitutes
            acceptance of the modified terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Open Source
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            Stand for Hemp is an open-source project. The code is available for review, modification, and
            distribution under the terms of its open-source license. See our GitHub repository for details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Dispute Resolution
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            Any disputes arising from these terms or use of the Platform shall be resolved through good-faith
            negotiation. If resolution cannot be reached, disputes will be governed by the laws of the
            United States.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Contact Us
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            If you have questions about these terms, please contact us at:
            <br><strong>contact@standforhemp.com</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-[var(--color-soft-cream)] p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Stand for Hemp is a non-partisan advocacy platform. We do not endorse
            political candidates or parties. Our mission is to empower Americans to speak up for the
            hemp industry, regardless of political affiliation.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="btn-primary inline-block">
          ‚Üê Back to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LandingLayout>
